# .audit-ignore — npm audit suppressions, consumed by scripts/audit-gate.mjs.
#
# Add an entry here ONLY when a high/critical advisory cannot be remediated
# right now (no upstream patch, false positive, dev-only path that is not
# reachable from production code, etc.). Every suppression is technical
# debt — link the tracking issue in the justification so it can be
# revisited later.
#
# Format
# ------
#   - One advisory id per non-comment, non-blank line.
#   - Valid id forms: GHSA-xxxx-xxxx-xxxx  or  CVE-YYYY-NNNN
#   - Each id MUST be preceded by at least one comment line (`# ...`)
#     giving the justification. The gate refuses to run if it sees a bare id.
#   - A blank line resets the "preceding comment" state, so each suppression
#     stands on its own.

# 2026-05-04 (UNI-29). vitest is a devDependency. The advisory only fires if
# a developer is running `vitest --api` and visits a malicious site in the
# same browser session — not reachable from the production Worker bundle
# (vitest never ships to Cloudflare). Fix is vitest@>=2.1.9, which crosses
# the pinned 2.1.8 and is bundled with the wider dev-tooling refresh
# tracked separately. Reassess by 2026-08-01.
GHSA-9crc-q9x8-hgqq

# 2026-05-04 (UNI-29). wrangler is a devDependency used by operators and CI
# at deploy time, never inside the runtime Worker. The OS-command-injection
# vector requires attacker-controlled flag values being passed to
# `wrangler pages deploy`; our deploy paths take inputs from version-pinned
# scripts, not external input. Patch lives in wrangler@>=3.114.x — cuts
# across the dev-tooling refresh; tracked separately. Reassess by 2026-08-01.
GHSA-36p8-mvp6-cv38

# 2026-05-04 (UNI-29). vite is a devDependency used by the SPA dev server
# only — `vite build` produces static files for Cloudflare Pages and vite
# itself never runs in production. The arbitrary-file-read vector targets
# the WebSocket interface of the local dev server. Patch lives in
# vite@>=6.4.2 (from 6.0.3); part of the dev-tooling refresh tracked
# separately. Reassess by 2026-08-01.
GHSA-p9ff-h696-f583

# 2026-05-04 (UNI-29). undici is a transitive devDependency of wrangler /
# miniflare. Both are dev/deploy-time tools; undici never ships in the
# production Worker bundle. The two high advisories are WebSocket-handler
# DoS / unhandled-exception conditions inside the local dev server.
# Resolution comes with the wrangler upgrade above. Reassess by 2026-08-01.
GHSA-vrm6-8vpv-qv8q

# 2026-05-04 (UNI-29). Same package and risk window as the entry above —
# undici WebSocket handler, dev-only exposure via wrangler / miniflare.
# Reassess by 2026-08-01.
GHSA-v9p9-hfj2-hcw8
